      "content": "- **Core scaffold:** fused bicyclic **indole-like** system (benzopyrrole). The `[nH]` indicates a **pyrrolic/indole N\u2013H** (not a basic amine).\n- **Functional groups:**\n  - **Carboxylic acid** `C(=O)O` (acidic; largely **deprotonated** at pH 7.4).\n  - **Aryl bromide** (Br substituent on the benzene ring).\n  - **Ethyl substituent** (adds modest lipophilicity).\n- **H-bonding:**\n  - **HBD:** indole N\u2013H (1), carboxylic acid OH (1).\n  - **HBA:** carboxylate oxygen(s) (1\u20132 depending on protonation); indole N is **not** an HBA.\n- **Structural alerts for CYP2D6 inhibition:** lacks the classic **protonatable tertiary amine** motif; no quinidine-like cationic center.",
