      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "### 2) REASON (SAR) \u2014 why features affect CYP2D6 inhibition\nCYP2D6 inhibitors typically present a **basic, protonatable nitrogen** (pKa often ~7\u201310) that can be **cationic** at physiological pH, enabling strong binding in the CYP2D6 active site (often via ionic interaction with acidic residues such as Asp301), plus **aromatic/lipophilic** features to occupy hydrophobic pockets.",
