      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "### 3) CONSIDER mechanistic basis (interaction with CYP2D6)\n- **Typical CYP2D6 inhibition mechanism:** reversible competitive binding where a **protonated amine** anchors (ionic interaction) and aromatic groups stack/hydrophobically interact near the heme pocket.\n- **This molecule\u2019s likely behavior:** could bind weakly via **hydrophobic/aromatic contacts** (indole ring + bromo-aryl) but lacks the **key ionic anchoring interaction**. The **anionic carboxylate** may also reduce access/affinity to the largely hydrophobic active site environment.",
